				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: A Retail Success for Instagram</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-12-15T18:03:48+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">December 15, 2014 1:03 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">December 15, 2014 1:03 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/12/15/today-in-small-business-a-retail-success-for-instagram/" data-title="Today in Small Business: A Retail Success for Instagram" data-description="The federal government spending bill quietly includes legislation affecting thousands of small businesses. Ten questions to ask before allowing employees to telecommute. And why retailers keep sending out catalogs.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Some believe that the increase in bottled wine consumption <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102244825">is a reliable gauge</a> of the economy.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is how one retail chain <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-12-11/brandy-melville-instagram-s-first-retail-success">built its business on Instagram</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-90917"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Senate <a href="//www.foxnews.com/politics/2014/12/14/senate-vote-on-spending-bill/">approves a spending bill</a> to keep the government running until September, and a writer says it <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/USA/DC-Decoder/Decoder-Buzz/2014/1214/Why-the-terrible-awful-nobody-likes-it-spending-bill-could-be-a-good-thing">could be</a> a good thing.</li>
<li>The bill <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/business/on-small-business/covert-operation-in-defense-bill-congress-quietly-passes-small-business-legislation/2014/12/14/3bf4361e-8097-11e4-9f38-95a187e4c1f7_story.html">quietly includes</a> legislation affecting thousands of small businesses and a huge <a href="//www.motherjones.com/politics/2014/12/spending-bill-includes-huge-insurance-industry-giveaway-too">insurance industry giveaway</a>.</li>
<li>Here are <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/12/14/eight-ways-the-new-big-government-spending-bill-affects-your-personal-taxes/">eight personal income tax provisions</a> still up for a vote in the Senate.</li>
<li>And here is a profile of President Obama&#8217;s <a href="//fortune.com/2014/12/14/meet-president-obamas-small-business-guru/">small-business guru</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A new kind of <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/12/13/small-bank-in-kansas-is-a-financial-testing-ground/?pa">mom-and-pop business</a> is trying to reshape the highly regulated and innovation-resistant banking industry.</li>
<li>This contest is looking for <a href="//info.kabbage.com/small-business-stories">small-business stories</a>.</li>
<li>The owner of a <a href="//www.greenbaypressgazette.com/story/money/2014/12/14/farmers-best-brings-milk-customers-doors/20377627/">milk and food delivery service</a> in Wisconsin explains how she runs the business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here are seven reasons <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/7-reasons-why-some-doctors-evgenia">some doctors</a> will never start a business.</li>
<li>This might be <a href="//qz.com/309042/a-better-formula-for-calculating-startup-equity/">a better formula</a> for calculating start-up equity.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Americans are <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/12/15/americans-are-trading-sleep-for-work-and-its-literally-killing-us/">trading sleep for work</a>, and it&#8217;s killing us.</li>
<li>Here are <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/231999?c">10 questions to ask</a> before allowing employees to telecommute.</li>
<li>The secretary of labor says there is â<a href="//www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/news/2014/12/12/u-s-secretary-of-labor-thomas-perez-on-jobs.html?page=all">upward pressure on wages</a>.â</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retailing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This is why retailers <a href="//www.npr.org/2014/12/11/369603493/heres-why-retailers-keep-sending-you-catalogs?">keep sending out catalogs</a>.</li>
<li>A store owner <a href="//www.al.com/news/huntsville/index.ssf/2014/12/huntsville_shop_owner_shares_j.html">shares</a> this âjaw-droppingâ video in hopes of finding a shoplifter.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Public relations <a href="//contentmarketinginstitute.com/2014/12/role-pr-content-marketing/">can play a complementary role</a> to content marketing, but beware of these five <a href="//thenextweb.com/entrepreneur/2014/12/13/5-common-mistakes-guaranteed-screw-pr-strategy/">common mistakes</a>.</li>
<li>Here are nine creative ways to add <a href="//blog.fundinggates.com/2014/12/9-creative-ways-to-add-a-customer-loyalty-program/">a customer-loyalty program</a> to any small business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Some residents of Los Angeles are upset at Google&#8217;s Waze for <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/locals-upset-at-googles-waze-for-sending-traffic-to-their-streets/#ftag=CAD590a51e">sending traffic</a> through their streets.</li>
<li>Mayor Rahm Emanuel explains how <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/12/12/smallbusiness/chicago-rahm-emanuel-innovation/index.html">Chicago saved</a> its small businesses.</li>
<li>Great Lakes ore shippers say theyâve had <a href="//www.crainscleveland.com/article/20141213/FREE/141219931">a good year</a>.</li>
<li>A January symposium in Rochester will explore <a href="//www.democratandchronicle.com/story/community/2014/12/13/21st-century-arts-presents-entrepreneurship-in-the-arts-symposium/20357567/"> entrepreneurship in the arts</a>.</li>
<li>The 15-year-old creator and chief executive of a Minecraft-based business in North Carolina has <a href="//www.newbernsj.com/news/local/young-entrepreneur-buys-toys-for-needy-children-1.413626">decided to donate</a> half a monthâs profit to Toys for Tots.</li>
<li>A 17-year-old New York City student <a href="//www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2873411/New-York-high-school-student-17-makes-72MILLION-trading-stocks-lunch-breaks.html">is reported to have made</a> $72 million trading stocks on his lunch breaks.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Stockholm&#8217;s tech start-ups are being <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/12/15/technology/stockholms-housing-shortage-threatens-to-stifle-start-ups.html">stifled by a housing shortage</a>.</li>
<li>Here is how President Obama could help Cuba&#8217;s <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/12/15/opinion/cubas-economy-at-a-crossroads.html">small but expanding entrepreneurial class</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Despite safety concerns, American taxpayers are <a href="//news.yahoo.com/u-taxpayers-help-fund-oil-train-boom-amid-121123189--sector.html">helping to fund</a> an oil-train boom.</li>
</ul>
